ot nerfed on the biggest hyped spell they were supposed to get  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serina Moonprism Elay</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have this spell got it on my second day in SOL. Its really nice. But DOES NOT stack with FOS or POTG. So its not really good for high end raids when you have a shaman and a druid around. But when you in a small group and neither are around then its great. It has like 300hp, 30ac, 6tick mana regan. <BR>Hope this Info helps. And yes it droped in Ssar Temple. Spell drops are crazy there. Until VI nerfs it of course. <P>------------------<BR>Serina Moonprism Elay<BR>60th High Priestess of Prophecy<BR>Property of Dastran Elay <BR>Member of the Elay Brotherhood<BR>Co-Founder of the Cute Club!<BR>Bertoxx Server<BR>"Be kind for everyone you meet is fighting a harder battle."-Plato <BR>"Insanity is the root of all genius." -Jen Meyskens</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Darianne</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>Just a heads up, hopefully others might have more or better info, but this zone recieved some "tuning" *cough*nerfage*cough*.<P>I did pretty much the exact same thing, as I did with my guild the night we had this, and many other spells drop... only this time, not a single spell, not even a crappy one.  All the loot, even those common fangs never dropped as much (but still did drop). <P>I'm hoping that all they did was move the spells to a higher level of the temple (or lower)... cause this blows.... maybe drops were too common before, but they blew it the other way I'm sure.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aerillea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Killed about a total 40 temple guards at the zone in and not a single spell drop.  I'